result.execSummary:
The defendant Alton J Janelle was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Alton J Janelle in court with attorney James E Goldmann.  Lesli S Boese appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Count 1,  Court finds defendant guilty. Ct. 2 dismissed and read-in.

Court orders the following: 
Ct. 1:
-  30 days  jail straight time STAYED for 1 year Probation - may be transferred to Dane County
- Court Costs of $343.00 (includes DVSurcharge) to be paid as a Condition of Probation 
- DNA Surcharge waived.
 Conditions of  Probation: No violent contact with Trisha J..   Domestic violence Counseling. Court will permit early termination of probation after 9 months if successfully completed and approved by the Agent. 
- Defendant to perform 50 hours community service as a Condition of Probation.
- 15 days jail Condition Time (nonworking hours) STAYED to be used at the Agents discretion. Huber/Straight time to be used at the Agents discretion. May be transferred to Dane County. No electronic Monitoring.
